Installation instructions for development machine 
==================================================
This project uses Python 2.7 and Fabric for installing software dependencies and managing the build process. The supported database is PostgreSQL.

In order to install Fabric, please run 'easy_install fabric' or 'pip install fabric' to get it. 
This demands a working C compiler (gcc), Python header files (python-dev), pip / distutils (python-pip) and sudo being installed. All of this is given anyway on a reasonable Linux box.

Make sure to check the supported Fabric tasks with 'fab -l'.

Preparation of the database
---------------------------
> psql
=# CREATE USER fuzztrees WITH CREATEDB PASSWORD 'fuzztrees';
=# CREATE DATABASE fuzztrees WITH OWNER fuzztrees;

Preparation of development machine
----------------------------------
> fab bootstrap_dev

Compile static stuff and prepare database
-----------------------------------------
> fab build.all

Run development web server and backend servers
----------------------------------------------
> ./manage.py runbackend
> ./manage.py runserver

Create install packages in ./dist on developer machine
-------------------------------------------------------
> fab build.all
> fab package.all

